·Skips files matched by pigeon_limits.is_excluded() — compiler orchestrators,
·prompt templates, intentional monoliths, vscode-extension entry points, client
·scripts, ∧ test harnesses are never auto-compiled.
·Called ← git_plugin after run_@_fix. Invokes run_clean_split on each
·oversized file, passing dead exports ↦ exclusions to the DeepSeek prompt
·so they are pruned ← the split output — never survive a compile cycle.
·Returns ⟨⟩ of dicts: {file, status, output_dir, error}.
·Does NOT loop ∨ auto-fix — produces a report ⟨⊃ targeted resolutions.
·Also handles dotted paths: `cognitive.adapter_seq001_v002_...`
·→ `cognitive.adapter_seq001`.
·Rewrites `← src.module_seq003_v003_... ⊕ Foo, Bar` to:
        ⊕ src_import ← _resolve
··Foo, Bar = src_import("module_seq003", "Foo", "Bar")
·This ≡ safe because src_import() resolves at runtime via glob,
·surviving any pigeon rename. No more naive ˢ.ℛ corruption.